---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Who is behind Climate and Eggs, and why.">

  <div class="max-w-2xl">

    <p class="mono text-xs mb-4" style="color: #7fff6e;">ABOUT</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-10" style="color: #e8e8e8;">
      Who, what, why
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: #aaaaaa;">
      <p>
        My name is Ege. I built this site because I couldn't find a resource on
        climate that I trusted — one that treated it as an engineering and systems
        problem instead of a brand positioning exercise.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most of what's out there is either corporate sustainability theatre,
        academic papers that take six months to be readable, or journalism
        that optimises for engagement over clarity. There's a gap between
        what's happening in the lab and what reaches people who want to
        understand it seriously.
      </p>
      <p>
        Climate &amp; Eggs is an attempt to close that gap. The Signal tracker
        pulls from peer-reviewed literature and surfaces emerging technologies
        before they become press releases. The writing is an attempt to think
        out loud about what it all means.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm based in Berlin. I'm interested in climate tech from an investing
        angle — specifically in finding what's real among the noise.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8" style="border-top: 1px solid #2a2a2a;">
      <p class="mono text-xs mb-5" style="color: #555;">GET IN TOUCH</p>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #555;">
        If you've found this useful, or if you think something here is wrong,
        I'd like to hear from you.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <a href="mailto:egeipek246@gmail.com" class="mono text-sm" style="color: #7fff6e;">
          egeipek246@gmail.com
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

</Layout>
